  "texts": [
    "For example, DropoutNet [24] and Heater [45] typically drop random behavior embeddings and use the generated embeddings instead of real embeddings during training to improve robustness.",
    "Rec [33] utilizes contrastive learning to enhance the compatibility of the generated embeddings and the behavior embeddings.",
    "However, existing solutions do not fully address the fundamental problem of cold-start-the lack of behavior data for cold itemswhich makes cold items inherently different from warm items.",
    "As illustrated in Figure 1, this fundamental difference leads to the following three key limitations:(1) Content-behavior gap: The synthetic embeddings are still derived from content features.",
    "This approach results in a significant discrepancy between these synthetic embeddings and the embeddings learned from actual user behavior and interactions."
  ],
